The Chairman of Nigeria Governors’Forum (NGF) and Governor of Ekiti State, Dr Kayode Fayemi has said he is confident that whoever emerges as the standard flag bearer of the All Progressives Congress (APC) would be the next president of Nigeria come 2023. Fayemi, a presidential aspirant on the APC platform made this known while addressing Benue party delegates at Royal Choice, Makurdi on Saturday. The Governor urged delegates of the party to vote for aspirants capable of bringing development and can also restore the hope of Nigerians, adding that whoever wins the forthcoming APC primaries would be President of Nigeria comes 2023. -Advertisement- Fayemi said, “Look at the mission of what I have presented to you. Don’t look at how many millions that we bring to the table but our commitment to democratic values and compassion; whoever wins the APC primary will be president of the country. Speaking on his programme of activities, if elected President, he said, “One issue am going to invest my time if voted in (as President) is to focus on security challenges; by this, we will re-jig the entire security apparatus of the country by recruiting more personnel and train the existing ones. “We will also need to improve on actionable intelligence and use satellite and growth technology to tackle security challenges. “Poverty and inequality triggered insecurity. We need to address all these and improve social investment in the people. We should also manage our diversity together every Nigerian will have a sense of belonging.” He also warned that “APC must take steps to address reward system in the party so that monkey will not be working and baboon be eating.”